{SECT 0 {PARA 256 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 18 "Elementary Algebra" }}{PARA 
256 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 14 "(number04.mws)" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 
203 "     In this exericse we study the basic properties of polynomial
s and rational functions.  Some revelant MAPLE commands will be    fac
tor, expand, solve, fsolve, denom, numer, simplify, subs,   ........" 
}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 320 "     The first thing we need to learn \+
is how to define a function.  There are two ways, each with its own ad
vantages and disadvantages.  First define the polynomial p1 as a symbo
lic expression in x in the following way:        p1:=x^2-1;  (Note the
 colon before the =, this is always required when defining something.)
  " }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 11 " p1:=x^2-1;" }}{PARA 
11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%#p1G,&*$)%\"xG\"\"#\"\"\"F*F*!\"\"" }}}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 105 "     Now define the same polynomial as a
n operation on the variable x in the following way: p2:=x->x^2-1;" }}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 13 "p2:=x->x^2-1;" }}{PARA 11 "
" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%#p2Gf*6#%\"xG6\"6$%)operatorG%&arrowGF(,&*$)9$
\"\"#\"\"\"F1F1!\"\"F(F(F(" }}}{PARA 257 "" 1 "" {TEXT -1 190 "Try the
 following command sequences to see some of the differences in how MAP
LE  treats these two definitions.  As always record your observations \+
and comments on the worksheet in text mode." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 3 "p1;" }}{PARA 11 "" 
1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#,&*$)%\"xG\"\"#\"\"\"F(F(!\"\"" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 
"> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 3 "p2;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#%#p2G
" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 6 "p2(x);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 
"" {XPPMATH 20 "6#,&*$)%\"xG\"\"#\"\"\"F(F(!\"\"" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 ">
 " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 8 "p2(t-3);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#,&
*$),&%\"tG\"\"\"\"\"$!\"\"\"\"#F(F(F(F*" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 14 "p2(u^3-u^2+2);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#,&*
$),(*$)%\"uG\"\"$\"\"\"F+*$)F)\"\"#F+!\"\"F.F+F.F+F+F+F/" }}}{PARA 0 "
" 0 "" {TEXT -1 5 "     " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 255 "     This wo
rks just like we expect substitution to work because p2 is an operatio
n on whatever is in the (  ).  However since p1 is a symbolic expressi
on we have some difficulties with substituting into it directly.   Try
 the following command sequences." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 6 "p1(x);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
{XPPMATH 20 "6#,&*$)-%\"xG6#F'\"\"#\"\"\"F*F*!\"\"" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 
"> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 8 "p1(t-3);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#
,&*$)-%\"xG6#,&%\"tG\"\"\"\"\"$!\"\"\"\"#F+F+F+F-" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "
> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 14 "p1(u^3-u^2+2);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 
20 "6#,&*$)-%\"xG6#,(*$)%\"uG\"\"$\"\"\"F.*$)F,\"\"#F.!\"\"F1F.F1F.F.F
.F2" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 148 "      Notice the extra x in fron
t.  This is curious and not very reassuring.  To substitute into a sym
bolic expression we must use the subs command." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 15 "subs(x=t-3,p
1);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#,&*$),&%\"tG\"\"\"\"\"$!\"\"\"
\"#F(F(F(F*" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 13 "subs(x=6,p1)
;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#\"#N" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "
" {MPLTEXT 1 0 6 "p2(6);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#\"#N" }}}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 4 "    " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 75 "     \+
Now let's do some simple operations on this polynomial.  In each case \+
" }{TEXT 256 46 "Explain what the command appears to have done." }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 
11 "factor(p1);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#*&,&%\"xG\"\"\"F&!
\"\"F&,&F%F&F&F&F&" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 11 "facto
r(p2);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#%#p2G" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> \+
" 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 14 "factor(p2(x));" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 
20 "6#*&,&%\"xG\"\"\"F&!\"\"F&,&F%F&F&F&F&" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "
" {MPLTEXT 1 0 10 "expand(%);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#,&*$)
%\"xG\"\"#\"\"\"F(F(!\"\"" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 
11 "solve(%=0);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6$\"\"\"!\"\"" }}}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 13 "fsolve(%%=0);" }}{PARA 11 "
" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6$$!+++++5!\"*$\"\"\"\"\"!" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> \+
" 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 12 "solve(p2=0);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "
6#\"\"!" }}}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 15 "solve(p2(x)=0);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6$\"
\"\"!\"\"" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 12 "solve(p1=0);" 
}}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6$\"\"\"!\"\"" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 
0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 12 "solve(p1=2);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6$
*$\"\"$#\"\"\"\"\"#,$F#!\"\"" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 
0 13 "fsolve(p1=2);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6$$!+330K<!\"*$\"
+330K<F%" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 12 "solve(p2=2);" }
}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#\"\"#" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 15 "solve(p2(x)=2);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6$*$
\"\"$#\"\"\"\"\"#,$F#!\"\"" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG 
{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 16 "p3:=a*x^2+b*x+c;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "
" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%#p3G,(*&%\"aG\"\"\")%\"xG\"\"#F(F(*&%\"bGF(F*F(F(%
\"cGF(" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 12 "solve(p3=0);" }}
{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#<&/%\"xGF%/%\"cG,&*&%\"aG\"\"\")F%\"\"
#F+!\"\"*&%\"bGF+F%F+F./F*F*/F0F0" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 14 "solve(p3=0,x);" }}{PARA 11 "
" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6$,$*(\"\"#!\"\"%\"aGF&,&%\"bGF&*$,&*$)F)F%\"\"\"F
.*(\"\"%F.F'F.%\"cGF.F&#F.F%F.F.F.,$*(F%F&F'F&,&F)F&F*F&F.F." }}}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 3 "   " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 4 "1.  " }
{TEXT 257 88 "Why did we need to include the ,x in the solve command i
n order to find the roots of p3?" }{TEXT -1 2 "  " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 107 "Use the solve command replacing x with a, b, c respectiv
ely.  You should be able to anticipate the results." }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 
"> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 
0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 4 "2.  " }{TEXT 258 58 "What's the famous formula we get when
 we solve p3=0 for x?" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 115 "Of course we co
uld have done the same exercise with the polynomial defined as an oper
ation.  Execute the following:" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 
0 19 "p4:=x->a*x^2+b*x+c;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%#p4Gf*6
#%\"xG6\"6$%)operatorG%&arrowGF(,(*&%\"aG\"\"\")9$\"\"#F/F/*&%\"bGF/F1
F/F/%\"cGF/F(F(F(" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 6 "p4(x);
" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#,(*&%\"aG\"\"\")%\"xG\"\"#F&F&*&%
\"bGF&F(F&F&%\"cGF&" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 17 "solv
e(p4(t)=0,t);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6$,$*(\"\"#!\"\"%\"aGF&
,&%\"bGF&*$,&*$)F)F%\"\"\"F.*(\"\"%F.F'F.%\"cGF.F&#F.F%F.F.F.,$*(F%F&F
'F&,&F)F&F*F&F.F." }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 60 "     Expand , then factor each of the following expressio
ns:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 10 "(x-3)(x+3)" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 
0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 12 "(x-3)*(x+3);" }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 
10 "expand(%);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#*&,&%\"xG\"\"\"\"\"$
!\"\"F&,&F%F&F'F&F&" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#,&*$)%\"xG\"\"#
\"\"\"F(\"\"*!\"\"" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 10 "facto
r(%);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#*&,&%\"xG\"\"\"\"\"$!\"\"F&,&
F%F&F'F&F&" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 12 "(ax+1)(bx+1)" }}{EXCHG 
{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 25 "(ax+1)*(bx+1);\nexpand(%);" }}
{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#*&,&%#axG\"\"\"F&F&F&,&%#bxGF&F&F&F&" 
}}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#,**&%#axG\"\"\"%#bxGF&F&F%F&F'F&F&F&
" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 10 "factor(%);" }}{PARA 11 
"" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#*&,&%#axG\"\"\"F&F&F&,&%#bxGF&F&F&F&" }}}{PARA 
0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 10 "(x+I)(x-I)" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 23 "(x+I)*(x-I);\nexpand(%);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
{XPPMATH 20 "6#*&,&%\"xG\"\"\"^#F&F&F&,&F%F&^#!\"\"F&F&" }}{PARA 11 "
" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#,&*$)%\"xG\"\"#\"\"\"F(F(F(" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "
> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 10 "factor(%);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "
6#,&*$)%\"xG\"\"#\"\"\"F(F(F(" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 4 "3.  " }
{TEXT 259 72 "Look at the last result and determine what number I repr
esents in MAPLE." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 172 "4.   See if MAPLE kn
ows a general formula for solving general cubic polynomials, i.e. Is t
here a 3rd order formula comparable to the quadratic formula?  If so, \+
exhibit it. " }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 29 "p := a*x^3 +
 b*x^2 + c*x + d;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%\"pG,**&%\"aG\"
\"\")%\"xG\"\"$F(F(*&%\"bGF()F*\"\"#F(F(*&%\"cGF(F*F(F(%\"dGF(" }}}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 11 "solve(p,x);" }}{PARA 12 "" 
1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6%,(*(\"\"'!\"\"%\"aGF&,***\"#O\"\"\"%\"bGF+%\"cGF+F
'F+F+*(\"$3\"F+%\"dGF+)F'\"\"#F+F&*&\"\")F+)F,\"\"$F+F&**\"#7F+F6#F+F2
,,*(\"\"%F+F'F+)F-F6F+F+*&)F-F2F+)F,F2F+F&*,\"#=F+F,F+F-F+F'F+F0F+F&*(
\"#FF+)F0F2F+F1F+F+*(F<F+F0F+F5F+F+F9F'F+F+#F+F6F+*,F2F+F6F&,&*(F6F+F'
F+F-F+F+*$F@F+F&F+F'F&F(#F&F6F&*(F6F&F,F+F'F&F&,**(F8F&F'F&F(FGF&**F6F
&FIF+F'F&F(FLF+*(F6F&F,F+F'F&F&*(^#F9F+F6F9,&*(F%F&F'F&F(FGF+*,F2F+F6F
&FIF+F'F&F(FLF+F+F+,**(F8F&F'F&F(FGF&**F6F&FIF+F'F&F(FLF+*(F6F&F,F+F'F
&F&*(^##F&F2F+F6F9FTF+F+" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 4 "5.  " }{TEXT 
260 111 "Why do you think high school students are never asked to reme
mber the general formula for the roots of a cubic?" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 24 "6.  For the polynomials " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "p[5]" "6#&%\"pG
6#\"\"&" }{TEXT -1 9 " through " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "p[18]" "6#&%\"pG6#\"#
=" }{TEXT -1 237 ", solve for all exact roots whereever possible, find
 all approximate roots to 10 decimal places, factor each into linear f
actors.  You will need to click on  [> in the toolbar to obtain new ex
ecution lines just below the cursor position." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {XPPEDIT 19 1 "p[5] := x^2-2;
" "6#>&%\"pG6#\"\"&,&*$%\"xG\"\"#\"\"\"F+!\"\"" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
