{TEXT 273 51 "What do you think quo and rem are abreviations for?" }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 
26 "pff:=convert(f,parfrac,x);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#>%$p
ffG,&#\"\"\"\"\"#F'*&F'F',&%\"xGF'\"\"$F'!\"\"F-" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "
" 0 "" {TEXT -1 89 "This is really just another way to write f.  To se
e that this equals f try the following." }}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 
1 0 6 "f-pff;" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6#,(*&,.*&\"\"#\"\"\")%
\"xG\"\"&F(F(*&F+F()F*\"\"%F(F(*&\"\"'F()F*\"\"$F(F(*&F0F()F*F'F(F(*&F
.F(F*F(F(F(F(F(,.*&F.F(F)F(F(*&\"#=F(F-F(F(*&\"#CF(F1F(F(*&F;F(F4F(F(*
&\"#?F(F*F(F(F0F(!\"\"F(#F(F'F?*&F(F(,&F*F(F2F(F?F(" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 
0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 12 "simplify(%);" }}{PARA 11 "" 1 "" 
{XPPMATH 20 "6#\"\"!" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 
"" {TEXT -1 5 "23.  " }{TEXT 274 49 "What do you think parfrac is an a
breviation for? " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 5 "24.  " }{TEXT 275 26 "
Look at pff and determine " }{TEXT -1 3 "   " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "limit(f,
x=infinity)" "6#-%&limitG6$%\"fG/%\"xG%)infinityG" }{TEXT -1 4 "   ." 
}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 36 "25.  Use MAPLE to verify the result." }
}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 22 "limit(pff,x=infinity);" }}
{PARA 11 "" 1 "" {XPPMATH 20 "6##\"\"\"\"\"#" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 107 "For demonstration purpos
es it is very handy to be able to construct polynomials with predeterm
ined roots.  " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 73 "26.  Use the expand comm
and to construct a polynomial with roots   1,2,2," }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "-1/
2" "6#,$*&\"\"\"F%\"\"#!\"\"F'" }{TEXT -1 71 ", 1+I, and  1-I.  (Here \+
the \"2,2\" indicates that 2 is a \"double root\".)" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 
